    <text>
        <body>
            <head>F30 [Gaede]</head>

            <div type="edition" subtype="fragment" xml:id="gaede.item_38" n="a" xml:lang="grc">
                <ab>
                    <seg type="context" resp="eust" n="1">
                        <ref target="urn:cts:greekLit:tlg4083.tlg001.stallbaum:890.5@ἀπὸ-890.5@φησιν">Eust. 890, 5:</ref> 
                        ἀπὸ τοῦ <geogName type="river" key="caresus" nymRef="Κάρησος Πίδυς" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/511287">Καρήσου</geogName> 
                        ποταμοῦ καὶ χώρα τις <placeName type="region" key="caresene" nymRef="Καρησηνή" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/511286">Καρησηνὴ</placeName>
                        λέγεται ἣν ὁ ἰδιωτισμὸς <placeName type="region" key="caresene" nymRef="Καρησηνή" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/511286">Κερασηνήν</placeName> 
                        φησιν.
                    </seg>
                </ab>
            </div>

            <div type="edition" subtype="fragment" xml:id="gaede.item_39" n="b" xml:lang="grc">
                <ab>
                    <seg type="context" resp="hesych" n="1">
                        <ref target="urn:cts:greekLit:tlg4085.tlg002:Κάρησσος">Hesych. s. v. Κάρησσος:</ref> 
                        <geogName type="river" key="karesos"><placeName type="city" key="karesos">Κάρησος</placeName></geogName>· πόλις καὶ ποταμός. 
                    </seg>
                </ab>
            </div>
            
            <div type="edition" subtype="fragment" xml:id="gaede.item_40" n="c" xml:lang="grc">
                <ab>
                    <seg type="context" resp="strabo" n="1">
                        <ref target="urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0099.tlg001:13.1.44@ἐμπίπτει-13.1.44@καλῶς">Strab. 13, 1, 44:</ref> 
                        ἐμπίπτει (Hercher ex συμπίπτει corr.) δ᾿ εἰς <rs type="river" key="scamandrus" nymRef="Σκάμανδρος" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/465994">αὐτὸν</rs> 
                        (scil. <geogName type="river" key="scamandrus" nymRef="Σκάμανδρος" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/465994">Σκάμανδρον</geogName>) ὁ
                        <geogName type="river" key="andiros" nymRef="Ἄνδειρος" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/550432">Ἄνδιρος</geogName> ἀπὸ τῆς
                        <placeName type="region" key="caresene" nymRef="Καρησηνή" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/511286">Καρησηνῆς</placeName>,
                        ὀρεινῆς τινὸς πολλαῖς κώμαις συνοικουμένης καὶ γεωργουμένης καλῶς, 
                    </seg>
                    
                    <seg type="context" resp="strabo" n="2">
                        <ref target="urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0099.tlg001:13.1.44@ὠνομάσθαι-13.1.44@ποταμοῦ">Strab. 13, 1, 44:</ref>
                        ὠνομάσθαι δὲ τὴν <geogFeat type="region" key="regionkaresos">χώραν</geogFeat> φασὶν ἀπὸ τοῦ 
                        <geogName type="river" key="caresus" nymRef="Κάρησος Πίδυς" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/511287">Καρήσου <geogFeat type="river">ποταμοῦ</geogFeat></geogName>
                    </seg>
                    
                    <seg type="context" resp="strabo" n="3">
                        <ref target="urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0099.tlg001:13.1.44@τὴν-13.1.44@ποταμῷ">Strab. 13, 1, 44:</ref>
                        τὴν δὲ <placeName type="city" key="karesos">πόλιν</placeName> κατεσπάσθαι τὴν ὁμώνυμον τῷ 
                        <rs type="river" key="karesos">ποταμῷ</rs>
                    </seg>
                </ab>
            </div>


            <div type="apparatus"/>

            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" n="1">
                <ab>
                    <seg type="context" resp="eust" n="a"><title>Eust. 890, 5:</title>
                        From the river <geogName type="river" key="caresus" nymRef="Κάρησος Πίδυς"
                            ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/511287">Karesos</geogName> also a
                        region takes <placeName type="region" key="caresene" nymRef="Καρησηνή"
                            ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/511286">Karesene </placeName> as
                        its name, to which the more common name of <placeName type="region"
                            key="caresene" nymRef="Καρησηνή"
                            ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/511286">Kerasene</placeName>
                        refers.
                    </seg>
                    
                    <seg type="context" resp="hesych" n="b"><title>Hesych. s. v. Κάρησσος:</title>
                        <geogName type="river" key="karesos"><placeName type="city" key="karesos"
                                >Karessos</placeName></geogName>: a city and a river.
                    </seg>
                    
                    <seg type="context" resp="strabo" n="c"><title>Strab. 13, 1, 44:</title> 
                        And into the <geogName type="river" key="scamandrus" nymRef="Σκάμανδρος"
                                ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/465994">Scamander</geogName>
                            streams the <geogName type="river" key="andiros" nymRef="Ἄνδειρος"
                                ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/550432">Andiros</geogName>,
                            coming from the <placeName type="region" key="caresene"
                                nymRef="Καρησηνή" ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/511286"
                                >Caresene</placeName>, a hilly region scattered with many villages
                            and beautifully cultivated, (...)
                    </seg>
                            
                    <seg type="context" resp="strabo" n="1"><title>Strab. 13, 1, 44:</title>
                        It is said that the <geogFeat type="region" key="regionkaresos"
                                    >region</geogFeat> takes its name from the <geogName type="river"
                                    key="caresus" nymRef="Κάρησος Πίδυς"
                                    ref="http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/511287"><geogFeat type="river"
                                        >river</geogFeat> Caresos</geogName> (...) 
                    </seg>
                
                    <seg type="context" resp="strabo" n="2"><title>Strab. 13, 1, 44:</title>
                        but that the <geogFeat type="city" key="karesos">city</geogFeat> which had
                                    the same name as the <geogFeat type="river" key="karesos"
                                        >river</geogFeat> was destroyed.
                    </seg>
                </ab>
             </div>
            
                
            
                
            

            <div type="commentary">
                <p>1) Gaede uses an edition of Hesychius where the toponym Karesos is spelt with one
                    sigma. We give the spelling for the lemma as it appears in Latte's edition
                    (Copenhagen 1953-1966).</p>
                <p>2) Hercher's emendation from συμπίππτει to ἐμπίπτει is difficult to render in the
                    translation.</p>
                <p>3) In Gaede's text the name of the river Andiros is spelt Ἄνδιρος instead of
                    Ἄνδειρος.</p>
            </div>

        </body>
